name: {{ .Name }}
version: 0.1.0
categories:
  - Misc
author: Unknown
description: A custom Wasm extension.
longDescription: |
  A custom Wasm HTTP filter built with the proxy-wasm Go SDK.

  ## Features

  * **Custom Header**: Adds a custom header to responses
  * **Configurable**: Configure the header value via JSON config

  ## Configuration

  Configure the extension with a JSON object:
  - `header_value`: The value to set in the custom header (default: "example")

  ## Building

  This is a Go module compiled to a WebAssembly module with the standard Go
  toolchain:

  ```bash
  env GOOS=wasip1 GOARCH=wasm go build -buildmode=c-shared -o plugin.wasm .
  ```
type: wasm
tags:
  - wasm
  - go
  - http
  - filter
license: Apache-2.0
examples:
  - title: Basic Usage
    description: Run the extension with default configuration
    code: |
      boe run --local .
  - title: Custom Header Value
    description: Configure a custom header value
    code: |
      boe run --local . --config '
        {
          "header_value": "my-custom-value"
        }'
